The objecctive of the project is to identify the factor's contribution to the prize of the used car.

so, here our mae i.e mean absolute error is 332.74

mae:= the mean absolute error is the diffrence between the predeiction and the true value of the observation i.e 0|Yi-Yi^|/n

mean squared error(mse)=: it measures how close a regression(straight) line is to a set of data point.

the worst part of the mse is it doubles i.e it square the outlires , so it is not robust to outliers.

root mean square (rmse) =: it basically measures for evaluating the quality of prediction . it shows how far predictions fall from measured true value.

r square (r2) =: it is the coefficient of determination.it basically evaluate the scattered data how much data is scattered
